<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Bus Crash in China Kills 12  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEIJING (AP) -- A bus carrying steelworkers home from their
factory ran off a road and fell 600 feet into a ravine in southern
China, killing 12 people, a state newspaper says.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred Saturday night in Guangdong province, the
Yangcheng Evening News reported Sunday. It said the driver was
making a turn but the report gave no other details on the
accident's cause.
</P>
<P>
   Seven other people were injured, the report said. The passengers
all worked at the Shaoguan Huang'an Steel Mill.
</P>
</TEXT>
