<HEADLINE> Mexico Opposition Party Wins  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Opposition candidate Vicente Fox won Mexico's
presidential elections Sunday, ending the ruling party's 71-year
lock on the presidency, President Ernesto Zedillo said.
</P>
</TEXT>
