<HEADLINE> Athletics 10, Angels 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Ryan Christenson hit a leadoff homer and
an RBI single during a seven-run first inning as the Oakland
Athletics beat the Anaheim Angels 10-3 Sunday to stop a four-game
losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Staked to a 7-0 lead before his first pitch, Tim Hudson (10-2)
improved to 9-0 in 13 starts since an April 20 loss at Cleveland.
Hudson, 21-4 in 38 career starts, allowed two runs and six hits in
seven innings.
</P>
<P>
   Christenson's second homer of the season triggered the big first
inning against Tim Belcher (2-2), starting the Athletics to their
21st win in 29 games.
</P>
<P>
   Belcher lasted just one-third of an inning, the shortest of 368
career starts, allowing seven runs, five hits and three walks. His
ERA ballooned from 4.97 to 9.67.
</P>
<P>
   In the first inning alone, the Athletics exceeded their run
total during the losing streak (six). Ben Grieve, Almedo Sanez,
Ramon Hernandez and Randy Velarde added RBI singles, and Miguel
Tejada had a run-scoring grounder.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Fyhrie blanked Oakland for 4 2-3 innings before Jason
Giambi's RBI single off Mark Petkovsek in the sixth. Miguel Tejada
added a two-run homer off Derrick Turnbow in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   For Anaheim, Garrett Anderson hit an RBI grounder in the first,
Tim Salmon had a run-scoring single in the third and another run
came in on Jeff Tam's wild pitch in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Troy Glaus was hitless in four at-bats to remain in an
0-for-18 drought. ... Palmeiro went 2-for-4 and is batting .369
(32-for-89) in 25 starts. ... Darin Erstad (2-for-4) had his 42nd
multihit game of the season.
</P>
