<HEADLINE> Giants 6, Dodgers 5  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Marvin Benard homered leading off the ninth
inning and Jeff Kent connected twice Sunday, leading the San
Francisco Giants over the Los Angeles Dodgers 6-5.
</P>
<P>
   Bernard hit a 2-2 pitch from Mike Fetters (3-1) into the
right-field bleachers for his sixth homer of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Winner Robb Nen (2-3) blew a save for the fifth time in 18
chances, allowing on a pair of runs in the eighth on Gary
Sheffield's RBI single and a wild pitch with F.P. Santangelo on
third.
</P>
<P>
   Kent increased his league-leading RBIs total to 80 as the Giants
won their second straight over the Dodgers after an 0-4 start this
year against their longtime rival.
</P>
<P>
   Kent homered off Eric Gagne with two outs in the fifth and off
Antonio Osuna with two outs in the seventh, raising his season
total to 23 with his 11th multihomer game, including two this
season.
</P>
<P>
   Giants starter Shawn Estes allowed one run, seven hits and four
walks in five innings. Estes allowed at least two runners in each
inning, walking the bases loaded in the third with one out. He
struck out Todd Hundley and retired Kevin Elster on a flyout.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Karros singled and Adrian Beltre walked to lead off the
fifth, but Estes was again able to pitch his way of trouble with
two strikeouts.
</P>
<P>
   Gagne allowed four runs, six hits and three walks in five
innings.
</P>
<P>
   San Francisco went ahead in the first when Benard singled and
stole second, continued to third on Hundley's throwing error and
scored on Bill Mueller's sacrifice fly.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Grudzielanek hit a game-tying RBI single in the fourth, but
the Giants took a 3-1 lead in the fourth on Armando Rios' sacrifice
fly and Rich Aurilia's RBI single.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles closed to 4-3 in the seventh on a run-scoring error
by catcher Bobby Estalella and Kevin Elster's RBI single.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Giants OF Barry Bonds was held out of the starting lineup
with a deep bone bruise in his right thumb, but was available for
pinch hitting. ... Shawn Green was not in the starting lineup on
Sunday for the first time all season. He did pinch hit in the
seventh and struck out, extending his slump to 3-for-34 (.088). ...
Kent has the most RBIs for the Giants in the first half since Kevin
Mitchell drove in 81 in 1989. ... Dodgers RHP Terry Adams, bothered
by soreness in his right shoulder, hasn't appeared in a game since
June 28 against San Diego. ... Dodgers LHP Onan Masaoka has not
been scored upon in his last eight appearances.
</P>
