<HEADLINE> Rockford Tops TV Detectives List  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RADNOR, Pa. (AP) -- Jim Rockford tops TV Guide's list of the top
25 television detectives from the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
   The character played by James Garner on ''The Rockford Files''
belongs in the top spot because he was sly, charming and
irresistible to fans, TV Guide says in its issue hitting newsstands
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Colombo, the rumpled Los Angeles detective played by Peter Falk,
came in second.
</P>
<P>
   ''I love him,'' Falk says of his character. ''He has a sly sense
of humor, is by nature polite and totally devoid of pretension.''
</P>
<P>
   Rounding out the top five are: Frank Pembleton, played by Andre
Braugher in NBC's now-canceled ''Homicide: Life on the Street'';
Mary Beth Lacey and Chris Cagney, played by Tyne Daly and Sharon
Gless in ''Cagney &AMP; Lacey''; and Theo Kojak, played by Telly
Savalas on ''Kojak.''
