<HEADLINE> George Mitchell Honored in Ireland  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) -- George Mitchell, the former U.S. senator
who guided peace talks in Northern Ireland, was honored Monday with
the Tipperary International Peace Award.
</P>
<P>
   Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern, who appeared with Mitchell at
the ceremony, said the award was a tribute to Mitchell's skill and
vision during his five years of involvement in the talks.
</P>
<P>
   ''Everyone who took part in the talks acquired huge respect for
George Mitchell, who encouraged all sides to contribute but was
also determined to build, brick by brick, a consensus that would
result in agreement,'' Ahern said.
</P>
<P>
   Mitchell's efforts paid off in the Good Friday agreement of
1998, which laid the ground for a new power-sharing government in
Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
   Previous winners of the Tipperary Peace Prize, established in
1984, include Nelson Mandela and Mikhail Gorbachev.
</P>
