<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WOODCLIFF LAKE, N.J. (AP) - Continuing its record breaking sales
streak, BMW of North America Inc. said Monday it sold 15,334
vehicles in June, a 6 percent increase over June 1999.
</P>
<P>
   The figures represent the 21st month in which the luxury
carmaker broke its previous year's sales performance. For the first
six months of this year, the company reported 98,783 cars sold, a
jump of 26 percent over the first half of 1999.
</P>
<P>
   BMW of North America, based in Woodcliff Lake, is the U.S.
subsidiary of the German carmaker.
</P>
<P>
   CHERRY HILL, N.J. (AP) - Senior Care Centers of America said
Friday that it has acquired Jeanes Vital Age adult day care center
from Jeanes Hospital in Pennsylvania.
</P>
<P>
   Senior Care Centers, based in Cherry Hill, now owns four adult
day care centers in Pennsylvania under the banner of Elderflower of
the Northeast. The Jeanes facility in Rockledge, Pa., will assume
that name as well.
</P>
<P>
   Founded in 1988, Senior Care Centers operates 16 adult day care
centers in New Jersey, Pennsylvania and Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   CRANFORD, N.J. (AP) - Mack-Cali Realty Corp. announced Friday
that it has acquired Parsippany Office Associates LLC as well as
full interest in Mack-Cali Business Campus and a portion of the
Morris County Financial Center in two separate transactions worth
$153.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   Mack-Cali purchased 5 Sylvan Way, 2 Dryden Way, 7 Campus Drive
and 2 Hilton Court. The four properties are part of Mack-Cali
Business Campus and Morris County Financial Center, both in
Parsippany.
</P>
<P>
   The Cranford-based company also bought 8 Campus Drive and 7
Sylvan Way, which are part of the Mack-Cali Business Campus.
</P>
<P>
   Mack-Cali owns or has interest in 266 properties in 12 states
and the District of Columbia.
</P>
<P>
   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) - New York-based Verizon Communications said
Friday it has named Dennis M. Bone state president in New Jersey.
He will work out of the company's Newark office.
</P>
<P>
   He succeeds William M. Freeman, who became president of the
company's public communications group.
</P>
<P>
   Verizon was created last week in a $59 billion merger between
Bell Atlantic Corp. and GTE Corp. The new company will provide
telephone service to some 95 million U.S. homes in 30 states and to
an additional 25 million wireless customers.
</P>
<P>
   FLORHAM PARK, N.J. (AP) - Richard P. Oths, president and chief
executive officer for Atlantic Health System since its inception in
May 1996, retired June 30. Joseph A. Trunfio succeeded Oths as
president, effective July 1, the health system said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Oths had a 30-year career in hospital administration. Before
joining Atlantic Health System, he was president and CEO of
Morristown Memorial Hospital, a 575-bed teaching hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Oths served as chairman of the New Jersey Hospital Association
from 1998 to 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Atlantic Health System, based in Florham Park, includes
Morristown Memorial Hospital, Overlook Hospital in Summit,
Mountainside Hospital in Montclair and Glen Ridge, The General
Hospital Center at Passaic and affiliates Bayonne Hospital and
Newton Memorial Hospital.
</P>
</TEXT>
