<HEADLINE> By The Associated Press  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Expect a sunny Fourth of July holiday statewide with
high
temperatures around 80 degrees. The only chance for a shower or
thunderstorm will be early and late in the day and only in the
southeastern part of the state, according to the National Weather
Service.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tuesday night will be clear with a low in the 50s.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday should be at least partly sunny statewide with high
temperatures in the upper 70s.
</P>
