<HEADLINE> Devil Rays Activate Castilla  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Vinny Castilla, who missed 17 games
with a sore back, was activated from the 15-day disabled list by
the Tampa Bay Devil Rays on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   To make room on its roster, the team optioned outfielder Quinton
McCracken to Triple-A Durham of the International League.
</P>
<P>
   Castilla, hitting .219 with six homers and 32 RBIs, returned to
the lineup against the Detroit Tigers, batting fifth. He had not
played since June 13 when he was removed after six innings against
the Anaheim Angels because of lower back inflammation.
</P>
<P>
   The third baseman, who turns 33 on Tuesday, was acquired from
Colorado in an offseason trade for Rolando Arrojo. He missed only
14 games with the Rockies from 1995-99 and had never been on the
disabled list before serving two stints this season.
</P>
<P>
   ''I feel good,'' he said before Monday night's game. ''I really
hope I can stay healthy the rest of the year.''
</P>
<P>
   McCracken, a starter two years ago who missed most of last
season with a knee injury, headed to Durham for the second time
this season. He hit .115 with two RBIs in 12 games for the Devil
Rays.
</P>
<P>
   Before leaving, the 29-year-old reiterated his desire to be
traded if he doesn't fit into Tampa Bay's plans.
</P>
<P>
   ''I want to play in the major leagues,'' McCracken said. ''The
next logical step would be for the organization to get something
for me.''
</P>
</TEXT>
