evacuated. Three of the injured were treated at the site, while the
fourth, a kitchen worker at the school, was taken to Kennedy
Memorial Hospital in Washington Township and treated for smoke
inhalation and released, Cardona said.
</P>
<P>
   The blaze broke out in a deep-fryer just before 3:30 p.m.,
officials said. It took 30 firefighters about an hour to control
the blaze that sent heavy smoke throughout the building, according
to Glassboro Fire Department Deputy Chief Ralph Johnson.
