<HEADLINE> Martinez May Be Ready for All-Stars  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Pedro Martinez may be able to pitch in next
week's All-Star game.
</P>
<P>
   Martinez, eligible to come off the disabled list during the
All-Star break, said he's on track to pitch next week. Martinez and
Toronto's David Wells are the most likely pitchers to start for the
American League on July 11 at Atlanta's Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   ''When I'm eligible to come off, I'll be ready to pitch,'' he
said Monday before the Boston Red Sox played the Minnesota Twins.
</P>
<P>
   Martinez is 9-3 with a 1.44 ERA for the Red Sox with 140
strikeouts in 106 innings. He went on the disabled list June 29
with a strained oblique muscle on his left side.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm sure we'll do the proper thing for me and the team,''
Martinez said, adding that he wouldn't pitch at Atlanta unless the
Red Sox give him permission.
</P>
<P>
   Martinez was the winner and MVP in last year's All-Star game at
Boston's Fenway Park, striking out five in two hitless innings in
the AL's 4-1 win.
</P>
</TEXT>
