faction. He also met Fazle-ur Rehman, who leads the ultraorthodox Jamiat
Ulema-e-Islam, a big supporter of the hardline Islamic Taliban rulers in
neighboring Afghanistan. There also were reports of a meeting between Musharraf
and members of ousted prime minister Benazir Bhutto's party.
