<HEADLINE> Marlins 2, Mets 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Mike Piazza's streak of 15 straight games with an
RBI ended Monday night when Derrek Lee hit a two-run homer in the
ninth inning to give the Florida Marlins a 2-0 victory over the New
York Mets.
</P>
<P>
   Piazza came close to extending his string, hitting a high fly
off the left-field scoreboard for a double in the eighth inning.
That stretched his hitting streak to 21 games.
</P>
<P>
   The major league record for consecutive games with an RBI is 17,
set by Ray Grimes of the Cubs in 1922.
</P>
<P>
   Piazza went 1-for-4 with three flyouts, the first two coming
with runners in scoring position. In the eighth, he got a second
chance when Lee, the Marlins' first baseman, overran Piazza's foul
ball down the line -- no error was charged.
</P>
<P>
   Starters Jesus Sanchez of the Marlins and Bobby J. Jones of the
Mets were gone when the game was decided.
</P>
<P>
   Florida won its fourth in a row. The Mets, who swept a
three-game series from the Marlins at home last week, have lost two
in a row after winning nine of 10.
</P>
<P>
   With one out in the Marlins ninth, Mike Lowell singled off Turk
Wendell (4-4). Lee followed with his 17th home run, a drive over
the center-field fence.
</P>
<P>
   Armando Almanza (2-0) got two outs for the win. He struck out
Melvin Mora with a runner on second to end the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Sanchez, who hasn't won since April 22 -- a drought that included
an 0-7 record with four no-decisions -- allowed four hits in eight
shutout innings. He struck out four and walked four.
</P>
<P>
   After Piazza doubled with two outs in the eighth, Sanchez
intentionally walked Todd Zeile and got Robin Ventura on a deep
flyout to center.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, who entered the game with a two-game win streak but an
8.10 ERA, gave up four hits in six innings. He walked none and
struck out five.
Notes: Despite a pitchout, Luis Castillo stole second when
Piazza's throw sailed into center. It was Castillo's 35th steal,
tying him for the major league lead with Colorado's Tom Goodwin.
The Marlins were 4-for-4 on steal attempts. ... Injured Florida RHP
Alex Fernandez, on the disabled list for the past six weeks, has
shown no signs of returning to the mound anytime soon. The soreness
in his right elbow and the back of his surgically repaired right
shoulder still prevents him from throwing of any kind. ... Sanchez
entered the game with an 0-6 career mark and 4.91 ERA against the
Mets. ... Jones was 0-1 with an 11.09 ERA in his previous five road
starts.
</P>
</TEXT>
