<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire 68, Fever 64  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Sophia Witherspoon scored 10 of her 20
points during a second-half rally, and the Portland Fire snapped a
five-game road losing streak with a 68-64 victory over the
Indianapolis Fever on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   The loss in the matchup of WNBA expansion teams was the eighth
straight for the Fever, who dropped to 1-8 at home.
</P>
<P>
   Sylvia Crawley had 16 points and nine rebounds, and Stacey
Thomas added 13 points for Portland (4-10).
</P>
<P>
   Monica Maxwell led Indiana (3-12) with 20 points, but scored
only three in the second half when the Fever missed 22 of 32 shots.
Rita Williams added 15 points for Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
   Portland trailed 47-33 early in the second half when Witherspoon
hit two 3-pointers, a short jumper and a fastbreak layup to fuel a
25-8 run over the next 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana regained the lead at 64-63, but went scoreless over the
final 1:29. Tully Bevilaqua hit three free throws for Portland and
Crawley made two more for the final margin.
</P>
<P>
   The Fever used a 10-0 run to take a 38-27 lead at halftime.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
